</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD3E3699FFCDFF9EFF3CFDF3FE5B8483" blockId="7.[191,1441,552,869]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
<bibRefCitation id="A9104B68FFCDFF9EFF3CFDF3FE5E8401" author="Gahan, C. J." box="[232,398,552,577]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" pagination="255 - 274" refId="ref14263" refString="Gahan, C. J. 1892. Additions to the Longicornia of Mexico and C entral America, with notes on some previously-recorded species. The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 1892: 255 - 274." type="journal article" year="1892">Gahan (1892)</bibRefCitation>
described this subspecies based on a male and females, not only males as reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="A9104B68FFCDFF9EFF6BFD92FEB88421" author="Monne, M. A." box="[191,360,585,609]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" refId="ref15341" refString="Monne, M. A. 2020. Catalogue of the Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of the Neotropical region. Part II. Subfamily Lamiinae. Available at https: // cerambycids. com / catalog / (Last accessed 24 June 2020.)" type="url" year="2020">Monné (2020)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="A9104B68FFCDFF9EFE73FD92FC9A8421" author="Tavakilian, G. L. &amp; H. Chevillotte" box="[423,842,585,609]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" refId="ref15705" refString="Tavakilian, G. L., and H. Chevillotte. 2020. Titan: base de donnees internationales sur les Cerambycidae ou Longicornes. Available at http: // titan. gbif. fr / index. html (Last accessed 24 June 2020.)" type="url" year="2020">Tavakilian and Chevillotte (2020)</bibRefCitation>
. There is no doubt about this because we have a photograph of a female 
<typeStatus id="123A883BFFCDFF9EFE30FDB1FD9784C2" box="[484,583,618,642]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">syntype</typeStatus>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="A9104B68FFCDFF9EFD5EFDB1FCE184C2" author="Gahan, C. J." box="[650,817,618,642]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" pagination="255 - 274" refId="ref14263" refString="Gahan, C. J. 1892. Additions to the Longicornia of Mexico and C entral America, with notes on some previously-recorded species. The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 1892: 255 - 274." type="journal article" year="1892">Gahan (1892)</bibRefCitation>
also commented that “… in 
<specimenCount id="DB87FD10FFCDFF9EFB5BFDB1FAC484C2" box="[1167,1300,618,642]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
example of the 
<taxonomicName id="0A814D1AFFCDFF9EFF24FD50FE7384E2" authorityName="Gahan" authorityYear="1892" box="[240,419,651,674]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Malacoscylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="humilis" variety="grisescens">
var. 
<emphasis id="FFF5EA8BFFCDFF9EFEFDFD50FE7384E2" box="[297,419,651,674]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">grisescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the punctuation is almost as much concealed as in the present variety [
<taxonomicName id="0A814D1AFFCDFF9EFACDFD50FEBF8483" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Malacoscylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="humilis" variety="flavescens">
<emphasis id="FFF5EA8BFFCDFF9EFACDFD50FA7084E2" box="[1305,1440,650,674]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">M. humilis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="FFF5EA8BFFCDFF9EFF23FD70FEBF8483" box="[247,367,683,707]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">flavescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
].”
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="859B6512FFCDFF9EFF3CFD17FC058525" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph id="CD3E3699FFCDFF9EFF3CFD17FA568564" blockId="7.[191,1441,552,869]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
We believe it is very probable that females of 
<taxonomicName id="0A814D1AFFCDFF9EFCF5FD17FBF884A3" box="[801,1064,715,739]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Malacoscylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="humilis" subSpecies="flavescens">
<emphasis id="FFF5EA8BFFCDFF9EFCF5FD17FBF884A3" box="[801,1064,715,739]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">M. humilis flavescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0A814D1AFFCDFF9EFBBCFD17FAA184A3" authorityName="Gahan" authorityYear="1892" box="[1128,1393,715,739]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Malacoscylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="humilis" subSpecies="grisescens">
<emphasis id="FFF5EA8BFFCDFF9EFBBCFD17FAA184A3" box="[1128,1393,715,739]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">M. humilis grisescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the same species. We did not see photographs of males of this subspecies. Accordingly, we do not know if they are 
<taxonomicName id="0A814D1AFFCDFF9EFE91FCD7FD848564" baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[325,596,780,804]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lamacoscylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis id="FFF5EA8BFFCDFF9EFE91FCD7FD848564" box="[325,596,780,804]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Lamacoscylus humilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or another species [equal or not to males of 
<taxonomicName id="0A814D1AFFCDFF9EFBA4FCD6FAA58564" box="[1136,1397,780,804]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lamacoscylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="humilis" subSpecies="flavescens">
<emphasis id="FFF5EA8BFFCDFF9EFBA4FCD6FAA58564" box="[1136,1397,780,804]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">M. humilis flavescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD3E3699FFCDFF9EFF3CFCF6FC058525" blockId="7.[191,1441,552,869]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
See comments under 
<taxonomicName id="0A814D1AFFCDFF9EFE3FFCF6FD578505" baseAuthorityName="Gahan" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[491,647,813,837]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schmidarius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvescens">
<emphasis id="FFF5EA8BFFCDFF9EFE3FFCF6FD578505" box="[491,647,813,837]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">S. fulvescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to understand the reasons for not designating a 
<typeStatus id="123A883BFFCDFF9EFB00FCF6FA928505" box="[1236,1346,813,837]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">lectotype</typeStatus>
for this species, and about the status of this 
<taxonomicName id="0A814D1AFFCDFF9EFDA9FC96FC9F8525" box="[637,847,845,869]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" rank="variety" variety="described">variety described</taxonomicName>
by Gahan.
</paragraph>
